---

- **Status of the test cycle: PASS** - The overall status indicates that all tests executed during this testing phase have been successfully passed without any failures. This is a positive indicator, suggesting thoroughness in our current QA process and product stability for release. 

- **Tests Run (15)** - Fifteen individual test cases were conducted within the last cycle to ensure quality assurance across different functionalities of Project XYZ. The variety should cover key features as well as edge cases, ensuring comprehensive testing coverage.

- **Passed Tests (15/15)** - All tests have passed without failures, signifying robustness and reliability in the software' end to meet user expectations upon launch. This level of pass rate can be attributed to effective test case design focusing on critical functionalities as well thorough code review practices within development teams prior to testing phases.

- **Code Coverage (85%)** - Code coverage refers to a percentage that describes how much source code has been tested in the last run, which is 85% for this cycle. While it isn't perfect and leaves room for improvement, especially concerning untested edge cases or critical functions not covered by automated tests, an 85% figure still indicates substantial testing coverage across project functionalities without significant code being overlooked during the QA phase.

